    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Peel and finely slice the\u00a0<strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Deseed the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>\u00a0</strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-chilli-con-carne/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong>\u00a0vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0over a medium heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the<span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong> chopped</strong></span>\u00a0<strong>pepper</strong>\u00a0and<strong>\u00a0onion</strong>\u00a0and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-chilli-con-carne/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the\u00a0<strong>garlic\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Dissolve the<strong>\u00a0beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>\u00a0in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\">\u00a0[400ml]<strong>\u00a0</strong></span><strong>boiled water\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Drain and rinse the\u00a0<strong>kidney beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-chilli-con-carne/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the\u00a0onion\u00a0and\u00a0pepper\u00a0have softened, increase the heat to medium-high and add the<strong>\u00a0ground cumin</strong>,<strong>\u00a0smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and\u00a0<strong>beef mince</strong></p> <p>Cook for 4-5 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-chilli-con-carne/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the\u00a0<strong>basmati rice\u00a0</strong>and 300ml\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span>\u00a0<strong>cold water\u00a0</strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p> <p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-chilli-con-carne/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong>\u00a0<span class=\"text-highlight\">to the mince</span> and cook for a further 30 sec</p> <p>Add the\u00a0<strong>beef stock</strong>, <strong>drained kidney beans</strong> and\u00a0<strong>chipotle paste\u00a0</strong>(Can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p> <p>Season with a generous pinch of<strong>\u00a0salt\u00a0</strong>and<strong>\u00a0pepper</strong>\u00a0and bring to the boil over a high heat\u00a0</p> <p>Cook for 7-8\u00a0min further or until thickened \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>classic <span class=\"text-highlight\">beef</span> chilli con carne</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-chilli-con-carne/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate the\u00a0<strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p> <p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p> <p>Once cooked, fluff the<strong> rice</strong> with a fork</p> <p>Tip: for extra indulgence, add a knob of butter to the rice!\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/classic-beef-chilli-con-carne/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong>\u00a0classic <span class=\"text-highlight\">beef</span> chilli con carne\u00a0</strong>over the\u00a0<strong>rice</strong></p> <p>Top with the\u00a0<strong>grated cheese\u00a0</strong>and garnish with the\u00a0<strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
